President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. These include Charles Benton, who is the Chairman and CEO of the Benton Foundation and has served on various boards related to media and telecommunications. Christie Pearson Brandau, a retired State Librarian and adjunct professor, has been nominated for the National Museum and Library Services Board. Bert Castro, the President and CEO of the Arizona Zoological Society/Phoenix Zoo, has also been nominated for the same board. Finally, William B. Schultz, who is currently the Principal Deputy General Counsel and Acting General Counsel of the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services, has been nominated for the position of General Counsel at the same department.